Utterances.UttText: Gerry Cage is a 46 year old M with history of HTN who presents after an episode of chest pain a few days ago.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 46 year old M with history of HTN
presents after an episode of chest pain

Utterances.UttText: He said he was carrying groceries when he felt substernal chest pain that caused him to drop everything.
The chest pain stopped after 5-10 minutes.
Notably, he has had 2-3 similar episodes in the past month, each of which he described as a ping of chest pain that lasted a few seconds and resolved without other management.

Phrases.PhraseText: 2-3 similar episodes in the past month,
described as a ping of chest pain

Utterances.UttText: Associated with lightheadedness, but otherwise denies syncope, trauma, vision changes or aura, SOB, abdominal pain, back pain, nausea/vomiting, leg swelling, or changes in urination or bowel movements.
Has had a few episodes of burning substernal chest pain following eating as well that are not associated with these episodes.

Phrases.PhraseText: a few episodes of burning substernal chest pain

Utterances.UttText: Denies history of anxiety or panic attacks.
Denies personal or family history of thyroid disease.
Dad had a heart attack in his 40s and had CAD.
Mom had HTN and T2DM and passed away due to PE.
Takes chlorthalidone and lisinopril for HTN - with good BP control at home and medication adherence.
Does not exercise, drinks a lot of coffee and has a poorly balanced diet.

BP 150/92 HR: 85 RR: 14 Temp: 98  General: well-appearing male in no acute distress CV: regular rate and rhythm; non tender to palpation of anterior chest wall Pulm: lungs clear to auscultation bilaterally with equal breath sounds.

Phrases.PhraseText: well-appearing male in no acute distress CV
; non tender to palpation of anterior chest wall

Utterances.UttText: Abd: non tender to palaption in all four quadrants LE: no edema  Gerry Cage is a 46 year old M with history of HTN who presents with 3-4 episodes of chest pain in the last month worsened by exertion and associated with lightheadedness.

Phrases.PhraseText: a 46 year old M with history of HTN
presents with 3-4 episodes of chest pain

Utterances.UttText: Notably, has FH significant for dad with CAD/history of MI at early age and mom with PE.
VS notable for elevated BP, but physical exam is unremarkable.
Arrhythmia: chest pain with positive FH  2.
Anxiety/panic attacks: less likely given lack of SOB and psych hx/inciting events 3.

Phrases.PhraseText: less likely given lack of SOB

Utterances.UttText: GERD: substernal chest pain that burns at times, but less likely to cause lightheadedness 4.
Stable angina: chest pain on exertion, none at rest  Will do EKG with possible ECHO.
May require a beta blocker.
Can trial pepcid for GERD.
